**Critical Engineering Principles to Follow Throughout:**

1. Design before code — every component must be fully designed on paper before implementation begins
2. State-driven agents — all agents communicate through a shared typed state object, never through direct coupling
3. Validate at every boundary — every input from users, every output from LLMs, every API response must be validated
4. Observability first — instrumentation must be built into every component from day one, not added after
5. Fail gracefully — every external dependency call must have retry, timeout, and fallback logic
6. User data isolation — every database query and vector search must be scoped to the requesting user's `user_id`
7. No hallucination tolerance — all LLM outputs must be grounded in the retrieved context and validated before being returned to the user 

